<div class="patternContent"><div class="patternTopic"> <h1><a name="OSG_Software_Release_3_1_24"></a> OSG Software Release 3.1.24 </h1>
<p />
<strong>Release Date</strong>: 2013-09-24
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Summary_of_changes"></a> Summary of changes </span></h2>
<p />
Changes include: <ul>
<li> osg-configure many bug fixes <ul>
<li> osg-configure now configures the Gratia probe for SLURM
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Completion of the Java 7 migration <ul>
<li> gridFTP-hdfs
</li> <li> xrootd-hdfs
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> osg-oasis now requires the latest oasis-config
</li> <li> osg-ce now requires frontier-squid
</li> <li> osg-configure warns when frontier-squid is not configured
</li></ul> 
<p />
 Detailed changes are below. All of the documentation can be found in the <a href="/bin/view/Documentation/Release3" class="twikiLink">Release3</a> area of the TWiki.
<p />
<a href="https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/issues/?jql=project%20%3D%20SOFTWARE%20AND%20fixVersion%20%3D%20%223.1.24%22" target="_top">11 JIRA tickets</a> were addressed in this release.
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Known_issues"></a> Known issues </span></h2>
<p />
There is a known issue (<a href="https://ticket.grid.iu.edu/goc/17182" target="_top">https://ticket.grid.iu.edu/goc/17182</a>) with HTCondor 8.1.1 which prevents Gratia from creating accounting records and may cause a loss of accounting information.  This issue will be fixed in HTCondor 8.1.2.  OSG sites are strongly recommended to avoid 8.1.1 until a Gratia patch is released with OSG 3.1.25.
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Updating_to_the_new_release"></a> Updating to the new release </span></h2>
<p />
You can update to this new release with:
<p />
<pre class="rootscreen">
[root@client ~]$ yum update
</pre>
<p />
<p />
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/help.gif" alt="HELP" title="HELP" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#ff0000"> NOTE </font></strong> </dt><dd>  Please be aware that running <code>yum update</code> may also update other RPMs. You can exclude packages from being updated using the <code>--exclude&#61;[package-name or glob]</code> option for the <code>yum</code> command.
</dd></dl> 
<p />
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/help.gif" alt="HELP" title="HELP" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#ff0000"> NOTE </font></strong> </dt><dd>  Watch the yum update carefully for any messages about a <code>.rpmnew</code> file being created.  That means that a configuration file had been editted, and a new default version was to be installed.  In that case, RPM does not overwrite the editted configuration file but instead installs the new version with a <code>.rpmnew</code> extension. You will need to merge any edits that have made into the <code>.rpmnew</code> file and then move the merged version into place (that is, without the <code>.rpmnew</code> extension).  Watch especially for <code>/etc/lcmaps.db</code>, which every site is expected to edit.
</dd></dl> 
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Need_help"></a> Need help? </span></h2>
<p />
Do you need help with this release? <a href="/bin/view/Documentation/Release3/HelpProcedure" class="twikiLink">Contact us for help</a>.
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Detailed_changes_in_this_release"></a> Detailed changes in this release </span></h2>
<p />
The <a href="/bin/view/Documentation/Release3/OASIS" class="twikiLink">OASIS</a> install of the tarball client now uses the CVMFS variable <code>OASIS_CERTIFICATES</code> to choose the directory containing CA certificates and CRLs.
The value for this directory is set in your CVMFS configuration files.
Installing the latest version of <code>oasis-config</code>, included in this release, will provide a default value for <code>OASIS_CERTIFICATES</code> that points to a certificate directory on <a href="/bin/view/Documentation/Release3/OASIS" class="twikiLink">OASIS</a>.
<p />
